Here’s the same remainder term in a single display-math block:

\[
\boxed{%
\mathcal{R}_{\sigma}(x_{0},t)
=
\bigl(\nabla f(x)\bigr):
\left\{
  \widehat{F}^{-\!\top}
  \left[
    -\frac{I}{\sigma^{2}}
    -\nabla_{0}^{2}\Lambda
    +
    \left(
      \frac{x_{0}}{\sigma^{2}}
      +\nabla_{0}\Lambda
    \right)
    \left(
      \frac{x_{0}}{\sigma^{2}}
      +\nabla_{0}\Lambda
    \right)^{\!\top}
  \right]
  \widehat{F}^{-1}
\right\}
\biggr|_{x_{0}=\Phi_{-t}(x)}
}\]

This is exactly the expression that multiplies the Lyapunov factor \(e^{2t\lambda_{\min}}\).

Here’s the same result trimmed down to bare-bones LaTeX so it should compile cleanly:

\[
\frac{\,(\nabla f(x))^{\!\top}\!:\nabla^{2}\rho(x,t)}{\rho(x,t)}
\;=\;
e^{\,2t\,\lambda_{\min}(x_0,t)}\;
\mathcal{R}_\sigma(x_0,t),
\tag{1}
\]

with

\[
\mathcal{R}_\sigma(x_0,t)
\;=\;
(\nabla f(x)):\,
\widehat F^{-{\!\top}}
\Bigl(
  -\tfrac{I}{\sigma^{2}}
  -\nabla_{0}^{2}\Lambda
  +
  \bigl(\tfrac{x_0}{\sigma^{2}}+\nabla_{0}\Lambda\bigr)
  \bigl(\tfrac{x_0}{\sigma^{2}}+\nabla_{0}\Lambda\bigr)^{\!\top}
\Bigr)
\widehat F^{-1}
\;\Big|_{\,x_0=\Phi_{-t}(x)}.
\tag{2}
\]

---

**Incompressible case (\(\nabla\!\cdot\!f=0\Rightarrow\Lambda=0\))**

\[
\mathcal{R}_\sigma(x_0,t)
\;=\;
(\nabla f(x)):
\widehat F^{-{\!\top}}
\Bigl(
  \tfrac{x_0x_0^{\!\top}}{\sigma^{4}}
  -\tfrac{I}{\sigma^{2}}
\Bigr)
\widehat F^{-1}.
\tag{3}
\]

---

*Notation recap*

* \(x=\Phi_t(x_0)\) is the Eulerian position of the Lagrangian label \(x_0\).
* \(F=\nabla_{x_0}\Phi_t\) (deformation gradient), \(\widehat F^{-1}=e^{-t\lambda_{\min}}F^{-1}\) with \(\|\widehat F^{-1}\|=1\).
* \(\Lambda(t,x_0)=\displaystyle\int_0^t \nabla\!\cdot\!f(\Phi_s(x_0))\,ds\).
* “\(:\)” is the Frobenius inner product, \(A:B=\operatorname{tr}(A^{\top}B)\).

This version avoids `\boxed{}` and fancy spacing commands, so it should render without the “group of unknown type” error.
